               <floruit notBefore="0001" notAfter="0100">He was an ancient king in the Horn of Africa whose rule extend to the
                  shore of the <placeName ref="LOC5339RedSea"/>
                  towards the middle of the first century. He is mentioned in the Greek Periplus of the Eritrean Sea as the ruler of the port
                  of <placeName ref="LOC1261Adulis"/>. 
                  Zoskales appears to have been an important supplier of ivory, tortoise shell, and rhinoceros horn, mostly from the interior regions to<placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt"/> and
                  <placeName ref="Q2277"/>. His kingdom provided a market for various imports, among them clothing, glass, brass, copper, iron, as well as axes, adzes, knives, 
                  drinking vessels, Roman money, wine and olive oil. 
                 
               </floruit>
            
